From 41280be969a4302d03866dd7721928ed5642fbd0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ying Xie <ying.xie@microsoft.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 19:44:28 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] [bmcweb] Pin sdbusplus wrap to known-good revision to fix arm64 build

bmcweb 6926d430 (2025-11-25) declares its sdbusplus subproject with
revision = HEAD in subprojects/sdbusplus.wrap, so each build floats to
whatever sdbusplus tip happens to be at build time.

sdbusplus commit eca33ec369c9 (2026-06-17, "remove type alias
sdbusplus::message::object_path") removed the long-standing
sdbusplus::message::object_path alias. With a floating HEAD, the SONiC
aspeed_arm64 build started pulling that newer sdbusplus and bmcweb
6926d430 no longer compiles, producing ~200 errors of the form:

    error: object_path is not a member of sdbusplus::message

Pin the wrap to 54d3b98e3c0d3dfbdd68a23cffe4de039548f337 (2026-06-16),
the last sdbusplus commit before the alias removal. It still defines
both sdbusplus::message::object_path and sdbusplus::object_path, so it
is compatible with bmcweb 6926d430 and produces a deterministic build.

References sonic-net/sonic-redfish#10

Signed-off-by: Ying Xie <ying.xie@microsoft.com>
---
 subprojects/sdbusplus.wrap | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/subprojects/sdbusplus.wrap b/subprojects/sdbusplus.wrap
index 7b076d09..d35c5cff 100644
--- a/subprojects/sdbusplus.wrap
+++ b/subprojects/sdbusplus.wrap
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 [wrap-git]
 url = https://github.com/openbmc/sdbusplus.git
-revision = HEAD
+revision = 54d3b98e3c0d3dfbdd68a23cffe4de039548f337
 
 [provide]
 sdbusplus = sdbusplus_dep
